# Implementation Plan - Secure User Authentication & Login Page (Issue 07)

We will implement a premium, theme-cohesive Login and Sign Up screen in the React frontend. Unauthenticated users will be directed to this screen. Once authenticated, the user's session will be persisted in `localStorage` and their custom username will be set as the active `userId` for journal entries.

---

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Authentication Options**:
> 1. **Option A (Frontend Session)**: A clean simulated authentication store in React. Entering any credentials creates a local session and logs the user in, using their username to partition data in the backend database. (No Go backend modifications required).
> 2. **Option B (Database-backed Auth)**: Full credentials verification by adding `/v1/signup` and `/v1/login` endpoints to the Go backend, storing hashed passwords in the database.
>
> *Recommendation*: We recommend **Option A** as a fast and lightweight solution that keeps data separate by username without complicating the backend server setup, but we can implement Option B if database-enforced security is required.

